Where oh where are you headed to world, only moving further and further away from God, your creator. The world would rather pay attention to this than to the signs of the world that are telling us we are in the end times. Jesus Christ is calling us to repentance but the world sinks deeper in its ungodliness. Oh but the pleasures and the ways of this world are far better, you say. Well they are only leading us to everlasting fire because no one seeks God and those of us who claim to believe in God do not KNOW God. We think He is ok with everything we do.  Everyone fights for a dream but few are the ones who fight for everlasting life. He is not okay with this ungodliness. These are all distractions from Satan to keep us away from God but we are unaware we see no wrong in the things we do because Satan has a veil over our eyes. He is pulling us all to the place destined for him and all wickedness and all ungodliness. The place of everlasting fire where the worm never dies. Repent of your sins and accept Jesus Christ as your Savior. Only in Him will we have hope to everlasting life. Believing isn't just with the mind. But with the heart. Repenting isn't just saying I'm sorry and continuing with our ways it means a change of life, a u-turn and putting your trust in Jesus Christ. It means to follow Jesus Christ and not the world. We will all have to stand before God. Will you be worthy enough to inherit the kingdom of God? The truth is none of us are. He will judge as all and because He is just he must give us according to our deeds. Jesus Christ died to pay for those deeds. It's a freely given gift but it's not forced upon anyone you accept it or you don't. Sadly most of us are accepting with our minds but not with our hearts, not with faith. We say we accept his salvation and continue with our worldly, secular  ways. That's not the point. Repent for then kingdom of God is at hand.
